  "Randall Rollins is chairman of Rollins Inc., the biggest pest control company by revenues in North America.",
  "Of the 19 subsidiaries under the Atlanta-headquartered Rollins Inc. umbrella, exterminator Orkin is the best known.",
  "His brother Gary, also a billionaire, is CEO of the $2 billion (revenues) company.",
  "The firm was created by Rollins' father and uncle, who bought several local radio stations and called it Rollins Broadcasting. It went public in 1961.",
  "The family ventured into pest control when it purchased Orkin in 1964, in one of the first leveraged buyouts in American history."
